  <title>Какие есть в Python фреймворки для web</title>
  <text xml:space="preserve"><note-content version="0.1"><link:internal>Какие есть в Python</link:internal> фреймворки для web

<link:internal>If</link:internal> you're coming from CGI development and planning a small app, I'll give a plug for the WebStack[<link:internal>1</link:internal>] framework which basically reduces just about every option out there (CGI, <link:internal>mod</link:internal>_<link:internal>python</link:internal>, built-in BaseHTTPServer, and several othes) to a common API.

However, I'd also recommend looking into one of the more powerful frameworks that abstracts away the server interface a bit more. I'm personally a <link:internal>Django</link:internal>[2] guy, but for <link:broken>some</link:broken> folks <link:internal>CherryPy</link:internal>[3], Pylons[4], TurboGears[5] or Zope[6] fills the bill.

[<link:internal>1</link:internal>] <link:url>http://www.boddie.org.uk/<link:internal>python</link:internal></link:url><link:url>/WebStack.html</link:url>
[2] <link:url>http://www.djangoproject.com</link:url>
[3] <link:url>http://www.cherrypy.org</link:url>
[4] <link:url>http://pylonshq.com</link:url>
[5] <link:url>http://turbogears.org</link:url>
[6] <link:url>http://zope.org</link:url>
[7] <link:url>http://twistedmatrix.com</link:url></note-content></text>
